<application>
 <id type="desktop">org.gnome.Paperwork.desktop</id>
 <licence>CC0</licence>
 <_name>Paperwork</_name>
 <_summary>All your personnal documents, scanned and PDFs, available in one click.</_summary>
 <description>
  <_p>
	Sorting documents is a machine's job. Paperwork is an easy-to-use application which allows you to find in all your documents what you need, when you need it. Type a few keywords in the search bar and the list of papers will shrink to only the relevant content.
  </_p>
  <_p>
	This is where the magic happens: Paperwork uses optical character recognition (OCR) to convert your papers into simple text files, so it's easy to search for text.
  </_p>
 </description>
